** Why Join Us: **

  * Part-time role with flexible hours! 
  * Conducive, and inclusive work environment 
  * Supportive work / study balance 
  * Development to support your career aspiration 

We have an exciting opportunity for a self-motivated, enthusiastic, and driven
** IT Support Officer Undergraduate (Part-Time) ** to join our dynamic team at
J&P Richardson Industries Pty Ltd (JPR). To be considered for this role, it is
essential that you are currently studying for your degree in Information
Technology. Along with joining a supportive IT team, there is an opportunity
for the successful candidate to work flexible hours, estimated 16 hours per
week.

Reporting directly to the IT Infrastructure and Applications Manager, this
role is specifically focussed on supporting the change and development of
digital forms and its associated data integrations across the business.

** What you’ll do: **

  * Provide IT support for IT users throughout the company; 
  * Configure new computers and mobile devices to the company standard; 
  * Assist in IT projects, including creation and migration of Digital Forms used across the company; 
  * Integrate databases and external systems into the Digital Forms platform, utilising scripting and custom applications; 
  * Work collaboratively with internal stakeholders to develop the digital solutions based on business needs; 
  * Assist other members of the IT team with technical requests; and 
  * Escalate requests to other IT team members as necessary 

** What you’ll bring: **

  * Intermediate knowledge of Microsoft products such as Windows, Office365, Outlook, Teams and SharePoint; 
  * Knowledge of computers and mobile devices; 
  * Enthusiasm and eagerness to develop firsthand experience of all things IT related; 
  * Effective verbal and written communication skills; 
  * Good interpersonal skills with the ability to work in a team environment and interact with a diverse group of people; 
  * Excellent customer service approach; and 
  * Ability to work in a fast-pasted dynamic environment. 

** Education & Experience: **

  * Currently enrolled and studying in a tertiary qualification (Degree) in Information Technology; 
  * Current Queensland driver’s licence (QLD) 

** About us: **

At JPR, we believe our people are the heart of our business and when they feel
valued and included, they #THRIVE!

We are one of Australia’s longest established Electrical Contracting and
Engineering firms, offering extensive local experience and proven project
delivery. This, combined with parent company Vinci Energies’ leading
technologies and global expertise, provides a unique platform encompassing
extensive local experience and knowledge, with the latest international
innovation.

To learn more about J&P Richardson Industries Pty Ltd, please visit **
www.jpr.com.au. **

** How to apply **

Applications must be submitted via SEEK and include a detailed resume with a
cover letter. Only permanent Australian residents need apply. Only shortlisted
candidates will be contacted for an interview.

